'''''Abitare''''', published monthly in [[Milan]], [[Italy]], was one of the world's best known design magazines.<ref>{{cite news|title=Magazine extols Miami's 'splendour'|url=http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=MH&s_site=miami&p_multi=MH&p_theme=realcities&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=0EB72DE291F35C6E&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM|work=[[Miami Herald]] |date=20 May 2000|accessdate=20 June 2009}}</ref> It was published between 1961 and March 2014.

==Profile==
The magazine was launched in 1961.<ref name=rcs>{{cite web|title=Abitare|url=http://www.rcspubblicita.it/site/en/home/media/magazines/abitare.html|work=RCS Pubblicita|accessdate=29 September 2013}}</ref> It was devoted to architecture, [[interior design]], furniture, [[product design]] and [[graphic arts]]. It is bilingual in Italian and English.<ref>{{cite news|title=Summertime 'Shelter' From Europe |url=http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/washingtonpost/access/74041118.html?dids=74041118:74041118&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Aug+04%2C+1992&author=Jerry+Knight&pub=The+Washington+Post+(pre-1997+Fulltext)&desc=Summertime+%60Shelter%27+From+Europe%3B+On+Vacation%2C+Take+It+Easy+And+Look+at+the+Pictures&pqatl=google|work=[[The Washington Post]]|date=4 August 1992|accessdate=20 June 2009|author=Jerry Knight}}</ref> Many known architects and designers were contributors to the magazine. Stefano Boeri is one of the former editors-in-chief of the magazine.<ref>{{cite web|title=Abitare magazine|url=http://www.lucapitoni.it/Abitare-magazine|work=Luca Pitoni|accessdate=29 September 2013}}</ref> Mario Piazza was also the editor-in-chief of ''Abitare''.<ref name=rcs/>

The magazine ceased publication in March 2014.<ref name=dez>{{cite news|title=Abitare design magazine-to cease publication|url=http://www.dezeen.com/2014/01/20/abitare-design-magazine-to-cease-publication/|accessdate=8 November 2014|work=dezeen magazine|date=20 January 2014}}</ref>

